      • getTypeOfVariable

        public String getTypeOfVariable(String variableName)
        Returns the type of a variable given its name. The method table is looked up first and then if the variable is not declared there, the variable is searched in class scope.
        Parameters:
        variableName - the name of the variable.
        Returns:
        the type of the variable given or "___" if the variable does not exist.
